When working with markdown files, always ensure compliance with markdownlint rules:

- Use consistent heading styles (prefer ATX-style headers with #)
- Maintain proper line length limits
- Ensure consistent list formatting and indentation
- Use proper link and image syntax
- Maintain consistent emphasis styling (prefer **bold** and *italic*)
- Ensure proper spacing around headers, lists, and code blocks
- Use consistent code fence syntax with language specifiers
- Avoid trailing whitespace
- Ensure files end with a single newline

Before finalizing any markdown changes, verify the content passes markdownlint validation.
